                            <comment id="12925204" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2010 23:53:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Two fixes to make:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Catch IllegalArgumentExceptions thrown by the BloomFilter and just continue writing the StoreFile without blooms instead of crashing&lt;br/&gt;
2) ByteBloomFilter.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;.bitSize should be a long and we should be able to handle large bloom sizes&lt;br/&gt;
3) We cannot handle byteSize &amp;gt; MAX_INT because java doesn&apos;t allow you to allocate arrays that large.  Throw an IAE in that case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12925227" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2010 00:56:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, added &quot;io.storefile.bloom.max.keys&quot; to control the max keys allowed in any bloom&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12925254" author="stack" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2010 04:16:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix Nicolas (I like the BBQ exception).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12925257" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2010 04:21:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lol.  I was trying to debug an assert failure that I had during unit testing.  You can obviously take that conditional out &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017628" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
